<headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 06 at 9:26PM EDT  by NWS Atlanta</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southwestern
Paulding, Haralson, north central Carroll and southwestern Polk
Counties through 1000 PM EDT...
At 926 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was over Mars Hills, or 10 miles
west of Buchanan, moving east at 45 mph.
HAZARD...Winds up to 40 mph and up to penny sized hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Buchanan, Bremen, Temple, Tallapoosa, Yorkville, Draketown, Felton
and Eubank Lake.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately.</instruction>
